    "native_c_aware_decode_is_per_step_correct": "With no row-chunk env set (pure native rows=N full-attention decode), both c4 and c8 pass the project correctness gate under teacher forcing. p95 per-step KL is ~0.003 for both; the vast majority of decode steps put the c>N batch distribution within ~3e-3 nats of the c=1 serial oracle and agree on the argmax.",
    "row_chunk_repair_not_needed_for_correctness": "The rowchunk diagnostic (c4 layers 3,15; c8 layers 3,7,11,15,19,23) was addressing free-running chaotic near-tie divergence (iter482), not a per-step correctness defect. Under the teacher-forced gate, native rows=4/8 is correct without any rowchunk.",
    "residual_near_tie_outliers": "A small number of near-tie steps produce larger per-step KL (c4 max 0.073 at row0/step67 with matching top-1; c8 max 2.575 at row5/step10 with a top-1 disagreement) and the rare top-1 mismatch (c4 99.41%, c8 99.32%). These are isolated single-step events consistent with chaotic near-tie sensitivity, not systematic error; the gate is on the mean and is cleared by >6x (c4) / >6x (c8).",
    "outlier_followup": "c8 row5/step10 KL 2.575 and the slightly elevated c8 row5 (mean 0.021) / row6 (mean 0.033) are worth a focused spot-check to confirm they are genuine near-ties rather than a row-specific effect, but they do not fail the gate."
  },
